body: @mama110 this repository can export to ONNX format, which is then interchangeable with practically any other format. I recommend you investigate importing ONNX format models into Android. We have an excellent iOS app, so it is possible for realtime YOLOv3 to work on a mobile device. This exploits Apple's A12 Neural Engine, however (https://www.apple.com/lae/iphone-xs/a12-bionic). I couldn't say what the performance would be on an Android device, but I suspect quite a bit slower.
